+{"id":"frankentorch-g95","title":"Relocate preserved beads recovery artifacts out of live .beads dir","description":"## Context
`br doctor --json` is operationally healthy now, but it still warns about preserved recovery artifacts because a backup DB remains under `.beads/`. The recovery data should stay preserved, but it does not need to live inside the active tracker directory.

## Goal
Move preserved backup/recovery artifacts under `artifacts/beads_recovery/` so `.beads/` only contains canonical live tracker files.

## Acceptance
- preserve all recovery artifacts
- remove `.beads`-local recovery artifact warning if possible
- keep `br ready --json` empty and sync metadata intact","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T20:04:52.090576188Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-03T20:06:34.486347834Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T20:06:34.486175568Z","close_reason":"Moved preserved backup/recovery artifacts out of .beads into artifacts/beads_recovery/live_cleanup, verified no beads.db.bad_* or recovery tree remain under .beads, and confirmed br ready stays empty; the remaining recovery-artifact warning in br doctor is stale tool-side reporting because it still references a path that no longer exists","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankentorch-gmn","title":"Implement index_add, index_copy, index_fill, clamp_min, clamp_max","description":"Add commonly used indexing/mutation operations: index_add (accumulate values at indices), index_copy (copy values to indices), index_fill (fill at indices with scalar), clamp_min/clamp_max (one-sided clamping). Used in sparse updates, attention masking, gradient clipping.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-27T20:19:01.847215240Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T20:23:19.870158728Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T20:23:19.869753691Z","close_reason":"Implemented clamp_min, clamp_max, index_add, index_copy, index_fill. 6 tests passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankentorch-gvc","title":"Implement count_nonzero, diff, cummax, cummin, repeat_interleave","description":"Add commonly used tensor utility operations: count_nonzero (sparsity analysis), diff (finite differences), cummax/cummin (cumulative extrema), repeat_interleave (sequence expansion). All used in training loops, data preprocessing, and model architectures.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:19:13.391108823Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T18:24:04.504011519Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T18:24:04.503763627Z","close_reason":"Implemented count_nonzero, diff (n-th order), cummax, cummin, repeat_interleave. 9 tests passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"frankentorch-gvt","title":"Implement tensor_bincount operation","description":"Add bincount across ft-kernel-cpu, ft-dispatch, ft-autograd, ft-api. Maps integer tensor values to counts. Critical for data processing, class weighting, histogram ops. Must support optional weights tensor and minlength parameter. PyTorch signature: torch.bincount(input, weights=None, minlength=0)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-27T05:43:08.617216568Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-27T05:48:53.006005299Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T05:48:53.005724498Z","close_reason":"Implemented tensor_bincount with weights, minlength, edge cases. 6 tests passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
